eNCA's Tumelo Mothotoane visited MacCarthy on his farm to share his vision for a Junior Farm Park, growing the number of young farmers and reveals the birthday gift he turned into a successful business. #DStv403 BRITS - Fred Junior MacCarthy, the 11-year-old farmer from Brits, in the North West appeared on The South African Morning a few weeks ago. Since then, South Africa has been fascinated with this young farming prodigy. He was recently invited to NAMPO, the biggest agricultural show in the southern hemisphere, and has gained the support of various agricultural organisations including government. eNCA's Tumelo Mothotoane visited MacCarthy on his farm to share his vision for a Junior Farm Park, growing the number of young farmers and reveals the birthday gift he turned into a successful business. * Watch the report in the gallery above.